---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const TREASURY_ADDRESS = '0xa668ddf22a4c0ecbb31c89b16f355b26ae7703c3';
const TREASURY_BASESCAN_URL = `https://basescan.org/address/${TREASURY_ADDRESS}`;

const SNAPSHOT_JSON_PATH = '/treasury.snapshot.json';
const LIVE_JSON_PATH = '/api/treasury.json';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Treasury Methodology — Anti Hunter"
  description="How Anti Hunter computes and displays treasury balances, cost basis, FMV, and receipts."
  canonical="https://antihunter.com/treasury-methodology"
  active="treasury"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
  </Fragment>

  <main class="stack-xl methodology-page">
    <section class="hero-simple methodology-header">
      <div class="eyebrow">appendix / treasury methodology</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">how the treasury dossier is assembled</h1>
      <p class="hero-copy">
        this appendix explains how the public positions table is computed, what sources it relies on, and where the best-effort assumptions enter.
        if anything here disagrees with chain data, chain wins. always.
      </p>
      <div class="link-row">
        <a class="link-chip" href={TREASURY_BASESCAN_URL} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">basescan wallet</a>
        <a class="link-chip" href={SNAPSHOT_JSON_PATH} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">snapshot json</a>
        <a class="link-chip" href={LIVE_JSON_PATH} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">live api</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="simple-grid cols-2 methodology-grid">
      <article class="section-card stack-sm">
        <div class="eyebrow">protocol</div>
        <ul class="list-clean methodology-list muted">
          <li><strong>never sell or swap $antihunter.</strong></li>
          <li><strong>fees in WETH</strong> fund inference, hardware, crypto, and NFT positions.</li>
          <li><strong>$antihunter</strong> may be used to pay community members for tasks and rewards.</li>
          <li><strong>protocol changes</strong> get 7 days notice for community feedback.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="section-card stack-sm">
        <div class="eyebrow">canonical wallet</div>
        <code class="wallet-code">{TREASURY_ADDRESS}</code>
        <p class="tiny muted">
          every important number traces back to a transaction. no exceptions.
        </p>
        <a class="link-chip" href={TREASURY_BASESCAN_URL} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">view on basescan</a>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="section-card stack-sm">
      <div class="eyebrow">field definitions</div>
      <ul class="list-clean methodology-list muted">
        <li><strong>Balance</strong>: current token balance held by the treasury wallet, using best-effort aggregation from the data provider.</li>
        <li><strong>Entry</strong>: earliest observed acquisition timestamp for the position. Some assets may have incomplete history.</li>
        <li><strong>Cost basis</strong>: inferred from on-chain settlement flows, mainly ETH and WETH associated with acquisitions.</li>
        <li><strong>FMV</strong>: current fair market value in USD from the pricing data source.</li>
        <li><strong>PnL</strong>: FMV minus inferred cost basis.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="simple-grid cols-2 methodology-grid">
      <article class="section-card stack-sm">
        <div class="eyebrow">source / onchain receipts</div>
        <div class="methodology-card-title">basescan</div>
        <p class="methodology-card-copy">
          base transfers, swaps, and balances are the source of truth. this site is just a reporting layer over those receipts.
        </p>
        <a class="link-chip" href={TREASURY_BASESCAN_URL} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">treasury wallet on basescan</a>
      </article>

      <article class="section-card stack-sm">
        <div class="eyebrow">source / pricing annotations</div>
        <div class="methodology-card-title">arkham intel</div>
        <p class="methodology-card-copy">
          the site uses Arkham's portfolio view and transfer USD annotations as best-effort pricing inputs for the reporting layer.
        </p>
        <a class="link-chip" href="https://arkhamintelligence.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">arkham intel</a>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="simple-grid cols-2 methodology-grid">
      <article class="section-card stack-sm">
        <div class="eyebrow">artifact / static snapshot</div>
        <div class="methodology-card-title">{SNAPSHOT_JSON_PATH}</div>
        <p class="methodology-card-copy">
          daily-generated JSON used by the homepage and treasury page when available. fastest path, lowest operational risk.
        </p>
        <a class="link-chip" href={SNAPSHOT_JSON_PATH} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">open snapshot</a>
      </article>

      <article class="section-card stack-sm">
        <div class="eyebrow">artifact / live fallback</div>
        <div class="methodology-card-title">{LIVE_JSON_PATH}</div>
        <p class="methodology-card-copy">
          real-time computation path. slower and more failure-prone than the snapshot, but useful as an explicit fallback.
        </p>
        <a class="link-chip" href={LIVE_JSON_PATH} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">open live api</a>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="section-card stack-sm">
      <div class="eyebrow">known limitations</div>
      <p class="methodology-note muted">
        pricing sources disagree. attribution can be incomplete. the point of this page is to make the assumptions explicit enough that anyone can audit them.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-clean methodology-list muted">
        <li><strong>Best-effort accounting.</strong> The table is a reporting layer, not audited financial statements.</li>
        <li><strong>Incomplete attribution.</strong> Multi-hop routes, aggregator bundling, and internal transfers can make tx-level attribution messy.</li>
        <li><strong>USD pricing drift.</strong> Third-party portfolio views can disagree with DEX spot or centralized exchange pricing.</li>
        <li><strong>Cost basis approximation.</strong> When the treasury spends $ANTIHUNTER to acquire other tokens, cost basis may rely on spot pricing rather than execution-time fills.</li>
        <li><strong>Chain truth.</strong> If you are verifying a claim, use BaseScan and the underlying transactions.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .methodology-page {
    padding-top: 2rem;
  }

  .methodology-header {
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .methodology-grid {
    align-items: start;
  }

  .methodology-list {
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
  }

  .methodology-list li + li {
    margin-top: 0.85rem;
  }

  .wallet-code {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    padding: 1rem;
    overflow-wrap: anywhere;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .methodology-card-title {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .methodology-card-copy {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .methodology-note {
    max-width: 54rem;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
